 The usage of HCC is very easy ! Just type in the program name, the option
 to let it know what it is supposed to do and of course the file it should
 handle. An easy expample next:

 HCC -c textfile.txt

 This will force HCC to create a new file called testfile.CAP with the
 contents of the old file converted into captial letters.
 Of course you can define your own destination file. This'll look like this:

 HCC -c textfile.txt newfile.txt

 Just type HC to get the options available displayed on screen.

 Interested users will also find the sourcecode of HCC.

